hopobject.body: Did you go to university? elearning.pharmacytoday.co.nz Old timers recall that receiving a telegram would be an event itself and the messages were normally opened with a sense of trepidation as people feared for the welfare of their near and dear ones. For jawans and armed forces seeking leave or waiting for transfer or joining reports, it was a quick and handy mode of communication. Lawyers vouched for the telegrams as they were registered under the Indian Evidence Act and known for their credibility when presented in court.
